name: sfchronicle
text:
President Trump calls extension on mail ballots ‘physically dangerous.' Bay Area faith, labor, and community leaders plan a “Protect Democracy” demonstration in Oakland from 12 to 3 p.m. on Wednesday. 

For more, follow our live updates:

name: sfchronicle
text:
Survivors of wildfires caused by PG&E in 2015, 2017 and 2018 may soon start receiving up to $25,000 they’re owed because of the company’s recent bankruptcy case —the first round of payouts from the estimated $13.5 billion settlement.

https://t.co/mJK6DUOGkq

name: sfchronicle
text:
There’s little doubt this has become one of the most divisive elections in recent history. In the largely liberal Bay Area, voters have turned out in record numbers and are anxiously awaiting results.
https://t.co/yKNcpTd45A

name: sfchronicle
text:
Tuesday is election day, but there’s no guarantee the country will know right away whether President Trump will be re-elected or Democrat Joe Biden will be the nation’s next president. 

Here’s what to look for while watching election returns: https://t.co/XmHf86UAPq
